main event: Witnesses observed a mysterious object in the sky over Dayton, Ohio on January 6, 1961, which appeared to be very fast and was later identified as a weather balloon.
interesting points: The object was reported to be the size of a quarter and moved quickly,The observation lasted for approximately 1 minute with a clear view for about 10 seconds,The witnesses evaluated the object and deemed it not to be an aircraft or astronomical phenomenon,The weather conditions were overcast during the sighting,The sighting was part of Project Blue Book's documentation of UFO reports.
sighted object: one object identified as a weather balloon
